      "id": "32124a91_80290003",
      "file_path": "/COMMIT_MSG",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 15,
      "message": "Both ways are fine to me\n\nSCP is tool agnostic: you can use dedicated plugin or generate config with \"vagrant ssh-config > ssh-config\" and then \"scp -F ssh-config $hostname:~/ternenv...\"\n\nSynced folders would also work but remember that it should support guest to host synchronization (e.g. rsync requires additional plugin: vagrant-rsync-back)",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5047,
        "name": "Pawe? Wieczorek",
        "display_name": "Pawel Wieczorek",
        "email": "pawel-wieczorek@outlook.com",
